	<td width="98%">
  
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>
		    <td valign="top">
		     <p><font face="Verdana" size="3"><b>Article Title:</b>&nbsp;</font>
		     <font face="Verdana" size="2"><b>New Poll Added</b></font><br>
		     <a href = "../Subscribe.asp?DID=546445" ><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		
		<tr><td>&nbsp;</tr><tr>
		
		    <td valign="top"><div style= "padding:4;float: right"> <script language=JavaScript src=http://www.obsidian-tech.com/absolutebm/abmx.aspx?z=26></script></div><p><font face="Verdana" size="2">
		    <blockquote>
Today, I added a new poll to the site to get some much needed feedback from you, the user.  I have 
received numerous emails recently asking us to make the message boards 
registered users only. We had contemplated doing this in the past but we always 
decided against it.  Now we have decided to let the community vote on this 
issue.<br><br>If you think the message boards should be changed so only 
registered users can post then go to our
<a href="http://www.everlore.com/polls/default.asp?mode=vote&poll=47">poll 
section</a>* and vote now.<p><font size="1">*Remember this poll also appears on 
the right hand side of the front page so feel free to vote their as well. 
</font></p>
</blockquote>
		    </font></p>
			 </td>
		</tr>
		<tr>
		     <td valign="top">
		     <br><font face="Verdana" size="2"><b><a href="UserUpdate.asp?id=546445">[Add Comments] Please Add your comments here!</a></b></font><br><hr>
			  </td>
